{
  "slug": "meteo_0",
  "language": "en",
  "provider": "claude-sub-agent",
  "model": "manual",
  "duration": 3031.2533125,
  "note": "Whisper base-model source had Swiss-German recognition errors; English is intent-faithful.",
  "segments": [
    {"i": 1, "start": 0.08, "end": 14.94, "text": "Hi everyone, I'm Fabio from Freewings and today we're going to tackle the meteo topic together."},
    {"i": 2, "start": 14.94, "end": 21.94, "text": "It's mainly about exam preparation, or meteo basics in general."},
    {"i": 3, "start": 22.16, "end": 27.16, "text": "There are basically two ways you can learn meteorology."},
    {"i": 4, "start": 27.16, "end": 31.16, "text": "One is the minimum effort, just for the theory exam."},
    {"i": 5, "start": 31.16, "end": 34.16, "text": "And of course there's a lot more weather knowledge"},
    {"i": 6, "start": 34.16, "end": 37.16, "text": "you can learn beyond that."},
    {"i": 7, "start": 37.16, "end": 40.16, "text": "There are basically no limits."},
    {"i": 8, "start": 40.16, "end": 43.16, "text": "There are five-volume tomes about meteorology."},
    {"i": 9, "start": 43.16, "end": 47.16, "text": "This course is really geared toward the basics."},
    {"i": 10, "start": 47.16, "end": 51.16, "text": "The course is also definitely useful for already-licensed pilots,"},
    {"i": 11, "start": 51.16, "end": 54.16, "text": "maybe to refresh weather knowledge,"},
    {"i": 12, "start": 54.16, "end": 56.16, "text": "or to learn some new things."},
    {"i": 13, "start": 56.16, "end": 60.16, "text": "There's definitely interesting material in here for experienced pilots too."},
    {"i": 14, "start": 61.16, "end": 65.16, "text": "But of course the course is mainly geared toward paraglider pilots,"},
    {"i": 15, "start": 65.16, "end": 69.16, "text": "so that you can hopefully apply this weather knowledge well."},
    {"i": 16, "start": 69.16, "end": 72.16, "text": "Where the theory might be a bit dry"},
    {"i": 17, "start": 72.16, "end": 74.16, "text": "and a lot of things are hard to understand,"},
    {"i": 18, "start": 74.16, "end": 78.16, "text": "we'll dive right in."},
    {"i": 19, "start": 78.16, "end": 81.16, "text": "Into this exciting field of weather knowledge."},
    {"i": 20, "start": 81.16, "end": 84.16, "text": "One thing that's always close to my heart,"},
    {"i": 21, "start": 84.16, "end": 86.16, "text": "especially when it comes to meteorology,"},
    {"i": 22, "start": 86.16, "end": 89.16, "text": "is that there are two areas."},
    {"i": 23, "start": 89.16, "end": 92.16, "text": "One is theoretical weather knowledge,"},
    {"i": 24, "start": 92.16, "end": 95.16, "text": "where you understand a lot of theory."},
    {"i": 25, "start": 95.16, "end": 98.16, "text": "But the actual weather plays out in practice,"},
    {"i": 26, "start": 98.16, "end": 100.16, "text": "and that takes a lot of experience."},
    {"i": 27, "start": 100.16, "end": 104.16, "text": "In flying practice, in meteo practice."},
    {"i": 28, "start": 104.16, "end": 106.16, "text": "Lots of it ties into the actual flying."},
    {"i": 29, "start": 106.16, "end": 109.16, "text": "The weather gets observed and analysed again and again,"},
    {"i": 30, "start": 109.16, "end": 112.16, "text": "and the theory is constantly cross-checked against practice."},
    {"i": 31, "start": 112.16, "end": 114.16, "text": "That's also really important."},
    {"i": 32, "start": 114.16, "end": 117.16, "text": "But in this section it's actually about theory"},
    {"i": 33, "start": 117.16, "end": 121.16, "text": "and about a basic understanding of weather."},
    {"i": 34, "start": 121.16, "end": 123.86, "text": "First of all, the biggest question:"},
    {"i": 35, "start": 123.86, "end": 125.86, "text": "where does weather actually take place?"},
    {"i": 36, "start": 125.86, "end": 128.86, "text": "That's our atmosphere."},
    {"i": 37, "start": 128.86, "end": 132.86, "text": "The atmosphere around the Earth is divided"},
    {"i": 38, "start": 132.86, "end": 133.86, "text": "into different layers."},
    {"i": 39, "start": 133.86, "end": 136.86, "text": "The stratosphere, mesosphere, troposphere."},
    {"i": 40, "start": 136.86, "end": 140.86, "text": "For us, the most relevant"},
    {"i": 41, "start": 140.86, "end": 142.86, "text": "is the troposphere,"},
    {"i": 42, "start": 142.86, "end": 145.86, "text": "where it meets the boundary"},
    {"i": 43, "start": 145.86, "end": 146.86, "text": "called the tropopause,"},
    {"i": 44, "start": 146.86, "end": 148.86, "text": "and in this layer"},
    {"i": 45, "start": 148.86, "end": 151.86, "text": "is where most of the humidity sits,"},
    {"i": 46, "start": 151.86, "end": 153.86, "text": "or most of the water vapour."},
    {"i": 47, "start": 153.86, "end": 156.02, "text": "And that's where weather happens,"},
    {"i": 48, "start": 156.02, "end": 159.41, "text": "in the troposphere."},
    {"i": 49, "start": 159.41, "end": 161.41, "text": "It's extremely thin,"},
    {"i": 50, "start": 161.41, "end": 163.41, "text": "if you look at it compared to the Earth,"},
    {"i": 51, "start": 163.41, "end": 165.41, "text": "almost like the layer of an onion."},
    {"i": 52, "start": 165.41, "end": 167.41, "text": "(unclear)"},
    {"i": 53, "start": 167.41, "end": 168.41, "text": "(unclear)"},
    {"i": 54, "start": 168.41, "end": 169.41, "text": "(unclear)"},
    {"i": 55, "start": 169.41, "end": 170.41, "text": "(unclear)"},
    {"i": 56, "start": 170.41, "end": 171.41, "text": "(unclear)"},
    {"i": 57, "start": 171.41, "end": 172.41, "text": "(unclear)"},
    {"i": 58, "start": 172.41, "end": 174.41, "text": "Like the skin of an onion,"},
    {"i": 59, "start": 174.41, "end": 176.41, "text": "it's really a very, very thin region"},
    {"i": 60, "start": 176.41, "end": 178.41, "text": "where the weather happens"},
    {"i": 61, "start": 178.41, "end": 180.41, "text": "and where we of course also move around."},
    {"i": 62, "start": 180.41, "end": 182.41, "text": "And as paraglider pilots,"},
    {"i": 63, "start": 182.41, "end": 183.41, "text": "we actually only move"},
    {"i": 64, "start": 183.41, "end": 184.41, "text": "in the very lowest layer"},
    {"i": 65, "start": 184.41, "end": 186.41, "text": "of this troposphere."},
    {"i": 66, "start": 186.41, "end": 189.66, "text": "And what's important in theory,"},
    {"i": 67, "start": 189.66, "end": 190.66, "text": "for the theory exam,"},
    {"i": 68, "start": 190.66, "end": 191.66, "text": "is knowing"},
    {"i": 69, "start": 191.66, "end": 193.66, "text": "the composition"},
    {"i": 70, "start": 193.66, "end": 196.66, "text": "of the gases in this troposphere."},
    {"i": 71, "start": 196.66, "end": 197.66, "text": "That is,"},
    {"i": 72, "start": 197.66, "end": 199.66, "text": "21% oxygen,"},
    {"i": 73, "start": 199.66, "end": 201.66, "text": "which is important for us"},
    {"i": 74, "start": 201.66, "end": 203.66, "text": "for breathing of course,"},
    {"i": 75, "start": 203.66, "end": 205.66, "text": "about 78% nitrogen,"},
    {"i": 76, "start": 205.66, "end": 207.66, "text": "and then there's about 1% noble gases,"},
    {"i": 77, "start": 207.66, "end": 210.66, "text": "for example argon,"},
    {"i": 78, "start": 210.66, "end": 211.66, "text": "but for us"},
    {"i": 79, "start": 211.66, "end": 212.66, "text": "for meteorology"},
    {"i": 80, "start": 212.66, "end": 214.66, "text": "that's not of great relevance,"},
    {"i": 81, "start": 214.66, "end": 216.66, "text": "the remaining noble gases"},
    {"i": 82, "start": 216.66, "end": 219.23, "text": "that are in there."},
    {"i": 83, "start": 219.23, "end": 220.23, "text": "Now,"},
    {"i": 84, "start": 220.23, "end": 221.23, "text": "the troposphere"},
    {"i": 85, "start": 221.23, "end": 223.23, "text": "is not"},
    {"i": 86, "start": 223.23, "end": 226.23, "text": "the same thickness all around the globe,"},
    {"i": 87, "start": 226.23, "end": 227.23, "text": "it's a bit thinner"},
    {"i": 88, "start": 227.23, "end": 229.23, "text": "at the poles"},
    {"i": 89, "start": 229.23, "end": 230.23, "text": "than at the equator,"},
    {"i": 90, "start": 230.23, "end": 233.23, "text": "which has to do with the Earth's rotation."},
    {"i": 91, "start": 233.23, "end": 236.23, "text": "At the equator it's roughly 18 kilometres,"},
    {"i": 92, "start": 236.23, "end": 238.23, "text": "and at the poles"},
    {"i": 93, "start": 238.23, "end": 241.23, "text": "it's about 8 kilometres."},
    {"i": 94, "start": 241.23, "end": 243.23, "text": "For us in Europe,"},
    {"i": 95, "start": 243.23, "end": 244.23, "text": "by latitude,"},
    {"i": 96, "start": 244.23, "end": 246.23, "text": "where we mostly fly,"},
    {"i": 97, "start": 246.23, "end": 247.23, "text": "let's say"},
    {"i": 98, "start": 247.23, "end": 249.23, "text": "roughly 11 to 13 kilometres"},
    {"i": 99, "start": 249.23, "end": 251.23, "text": "thickness of this troposphere,"},
    {"i": 100, "start": 251.23, "end": 257.86, "text": "let's say 13,000 metres."},
    {"i": 101, "start": 257.86, "end": 259.15, "text": "Now,"},
    {"i": 102, "start": 259.15, "end": 261.15, "text": "let's talk about the standard atmosphere."},
    {"i": 103, "start": 261.15, "end": 263.15, "text": "This is always important,"},
    {"i": 104, "start": 263.15, "end": 264.15, "text": "in flight weather"},
    {"i": 105, "start": 264.15, "end": 266.15, "text": "and especially the theory exam"},
    {"i": 106, "start": 266.15, "end": 268.15, "text": "keeps asking"},
    {"i": 107, "start": 268.15, "end": 270.15, "text": "about the standard atmosphere."},
    {"i": 108, "start": 270.15, "end": 273.15, "text": "That's the atmosphere"},
    {"i": 109, "start": 273.15, "end": 275.15, "text": "where weather"},
    {"i": 110, "start": 275.15, "end": 276.15, "text": "has completely balanced out,"},
    {"i": 111, "start": 276.15, "end": 278.15, "text": "we have no high-pressure areas,"},
    {"i": 112, "start": 278.15, "end": 279.15, "text": "no low-pressure areas,"},
    {"i": 113, "start": 279.15, "end": 280.15, "text": "and different factors"},
    {"i": 114, "start": 280.15, "end": 282.15, "text": "that influence us from outside."},
    {"i": 115, "start": 282.15, "end": 283.15, "text": "We'll look at those."},
    {"i": 116, "start": 283.15, "end": 285.15, "text": "When everything has balanced out,"},
    {"i": 117, "start": 285.15, "end": 289.15, "text": "we arrive at what's called the standard atmosphere."},
    {"i": 118, "start": 289.15, "end": 291.15, "text": "It's basically a zero point,"},
    {"i": 119, "start": 291.15, "end": 293.15, "text": "where everything has equalised."},
    {"i": 120, "start": 293.15, "end": 295.15, "text": "And there are a few numbers"},
    {"i": 121, "start": 295.15, "end": 296.15, "text": "and facts,"},
    {"i": 122, "start": 296.15, "end": 300.15, "text": "that the theory exam asks for."},
    {"i": 123, "start": 300.15, "end": 305.7, "text": "The important one is the temperature gradient with altitude,"},
    {"i": 124, "start": 305.7, "end": 309.7, "text": "how the troposphere cools off."},
    {"i": 125, "start": 309.7, "end": 312.7, "text": "We say 6.5 degrees"},
    {"i": 126, "start": 312.7, "end": 314.7, "text": "per 1000 metres of altitude,"},
    {"i": 127, "start": 314.7, "end": 315.7, "text": "or per 100 metres,"},
    {"i": 128, "start": 315.7, "end": 316.7, "text": "you can also say it as"},
    {"i": 129, "start": 316.7, "end": 322.7, "text": "0.65 degrees per 100 metres."},
    {"i": 130, "start": 322.7, "end": 324.76, "text": "Then at the surface,"},
    {"i": 131, "start": 324.76, "end": 325.76, "text": "in the standard atmosphere,"},
    {"i": 132, "start": 325.76, "end": 327.76, "text": "we talk about 15 degrees,"},
    {"i": 133, "start": 327.76, "end": 329.76, "text": "and at the tropopause"},
    {"i": 134, "start": 329.76, "end": 331.76, "text": "about minus 56 degrees."},
    {"i": 135, "start": 331.76, "end": 334.76, "text": "Especially those two numbers are important,"},
    {"i": 136, "start": 334.76, "end": 338.76, "text": "to learn for the theory exam."},
    {"i": 137, "start": 338.76, "end": 348.34, "text": "The temperature gradient,"},
    {"i": 138, "start": 348.34, "end": 350.34, "text": "depending on the weather situation,"},
    {"i": 139, "start": 350.34, "end": 351.34, "text": "and the conditions,"},
    {"i": 140, "start": 351.34, "end": 352.34, "text": "as you'll learn later,"},
    {"i": 141, "start": 352.34, "end": 354.62, "text": "can of course vary."},
    {"i": 142, "start": 354.62, "end": 357.62, "text": "But for the standard atmosphere we say 6.5 degrees"},
    {"i": 143, "start": 357.62, "end": 359.62, "text": "per 100 metres."},
    {"i": 144, "start": 359.62, "end": 361.62, "text": "That's the temperature."},
    {"i": 145, "start": 361.62, "end": 363.62, "text": "In the standard atmosphere we also talk about,"},
    {"i": 146, "start": 363.62, "end": 364.62, "text": "the standard pressure,"},
    {"i": 147, "start": 364.62, "end": 365.62, "text": "and the numbers"},
    {"i": 148, "start": 365.62, "end": 367.62, "text": "you'll hear again and again,"},
    {"i": 149, "start": 367.62, "end": 370.62, "text": "are 1013.25 hectopascals."},
    {"i": 150, "start": 370.62, "end": 371.62, "text": "The air pressure,"},
    {"i": 151, "start": 371.62, "end": 374.62, "text": "when the whole troposphere"},
    {"i": 152, "start": 374.62, "end": 375.62, "text": "is in balance,"},
    {"i": 153, "start": 375.62, "end": 378.62, "text": "calculated at sea level,"},
    {"i": 154, "start": 378.62, "end": 380.62, "text": "the air pressure is always the same,"},
    {"i": 155, "start": 380.62, "end": 383.62, "text": "namely 1013.25 hectopascals."},
    {"i": 156, "start": 383.62, "end": 385.62, "text": "And the troposphere height,"},
    {"i": 157, "start": 385.62, "end": 386.62, "text": "the highest,"},
    {"i": 158, "start": 386.62, "end": 388.62, "text": "where the tropopause begins,"},
    {"i": 159, "start": 388.62, "end": 391.62, "text": "is at 11 kilometres in the standard atmosphere."},
    {"i": 160, "start": 393.42, "end": 395.42, "text": "Another important thing about air pressure,"},
    {"i": 161, "start": 395.42, "end": 397.42, "text": "how it decreases with altitude,"},
    {"i": 162, "start": 397.42, "end": 398.42, "text": "is not linear,"},
    {"i": 163, "start": 398.42, "end": 400.42, "text": "there's a rule of thumb."},
    {"i": 164, "start": 400.42, "end": 401.42, "text": "We can say that"},
    {"i": 165, "start": 401.42, "end": 405.42, "text": "every 5500 metres of altitude"},
    {"i": 166, "start": 405.42, "end": 407.42, "text": "the air pressure halves."},
    {"i": 167, "start": 407.42, "end": 409.42, "text": "So we can say,"},
    {"i": 168, "start": 409.42, "end": 410.42, "text": "at 5500 metres,"},
    {"i": 169, "start": 410.42, "end": 411.42, "text": "you'd have about 500,"},
    {"i": 170, "start": 411.42, "end": 414.42, "text": "or 506 hectopascals."},
    {"i": 171, "start": 414.42, "end": 415.71, "text": "That's also a value,"},
    {"i": 172, "start": 415.71, "end": 417.71, "text": "the 5500 metres,"},
    {"i": 173, "start": 417.71, "end": 419.71, "text": "that's very important,"},
    {"i": 174, "start": 419.71, "end": 420.71, "text": "for the theory exam,"},
    {"i": 175, "start": 420.71, "end": 421.71, "text": "to learn."},
    {"i": 176, "start": 421.71, "end": 424.71, "text": "So pressure of course decreases with altitude."},
    {"i": 177, "start": 424.71, "end": 426.71, "text": "You can picture air pressure"},
    {"i": 178, "start": 426.71, "end": 428.71, "text": "as a column of air"},
    {"i": 179, "start": 428.71, "end": 429.71, "text": "above you,"},
    {"i": 180, "start": 429.71, "end": 431.71, "text": "all the way up to the tropopause."},
    {"i": 181, "start": 431.71, "end": 433.71, "text": "And it's the same as water, for example,"},
    {"i": 182, "start": 433.71, "end": 435.71, "text": "those who dive will know:"},
    {"i": 183, "start": 435.71, "end": 437.71, "text": "the deeper you go in the water,"},
    {"i": 184, "start": 437.71, "end": 439.71, "text": "the higher the pressure,"},
    {"i": 185, "start": 439.71, "end": 441.71, "text": "the gravity of the Earth."},
    {"i": 186, "start": 441.71, "end": 442.71, "text": "And so we can say,"},
    {"i": 187, "start": 442.71, "end": 444.71, "text": "the air pressure is of course"},
    {"i": 188, "start": 444.71, "end": 446.71, "text": "highest at the lowest point,"},
    {"i": 189, "start": 446.71, "end": 447.71, "text": "at sea level,"},
    {"i": 190, "start": 447.71, "end": 449.71, "text": "and decreases with altitude."},
    {"i": 191, "start": 449.71, "end": 451.71, "text": "That has to do with gravity"},
    {"i": 192, "start": 451.71, "end": 453.74, "text": "and with this column of air"},
    {"i": 193, "start": 453.74, "end": 455.74, "text": "that presses down on us"},
    {"i": 194, "start": 455.74, "end": 456.74, "text": "and so to speak"},
    {"i": 195, "start": 456.74, "end": 458.74, "text": "generates air pressure."},
    {"i": 196, "start": 458.74, "end": 460.74, "text": "Quick summary of the numbers:"},
    {"i": 197, "start": 460.74, "end": 463.74, "text": "1013.25, 15 degrees,"},
    {"i": 198, "start": 463.74, "end": 466.74, "text": "and 0.65 per 100 metres,"},
    {"i": 199, "start": 466.74, "end": 468.74, "text": "those are the numbers"},
    {"i": 200, "start": 468.74, "end": 470.74, "text": "that are relevant for us"},
    {"i": 201, "start": 470.74, "end": 473.74, "text": "for the standard atmosphere."},
    {"i": 202, "start": 474.38, "end": 475.38, "text": "Right."},
    {"i": 203, "start": 475.38, "end": 476.42, "text": "And if you think about it,"},
    {"i": 204, "start": 476.42, "end": 478.42, "text": "the standard atmosphere"},
    {"i": 205, "start": 478.42, "end": 480.42, "text": "is of course not always the same,"},
    {"i": 206, "start": 480.42, "end": 482.42, "text": "as we experience daily"},
    {"i": 207, "start": 482.42, "end": 484.42, "text": "with the weather."},
    {"i": 208, "start": 484.42, "end": 486.42, "text": "There's a motor that drives this,"},
    {"i": 209, "start": 486.42, "end": 488.42, "text": "the sun that shines on the Earth,"},
    {"i": 210, "start": 488.42, "end": 489.42, "text": "and acts on it,"},
    {"i": 211, "start": 489.42, "end": 491.42, "text": "different land masses,"},
    {"i": 212, "start": 491.42, "end": 493.42, "text": "and more water,"},
    {"i": 213, "start": 493.42, "end": 495.42, "text": "different heating,"},
    {"i": 214, "start": 495.42, "end": 497.42, "text": "different seasons too,"},
    {"i": 215, "start": 497.42, "end": 499.42, "text": "with different sun angles depending on the season."},
    {"i": 216, "start": 499.42, "end": 502.42, "text": "The sun isn't always at the same height."},
    {"i": 217, "start": 502.42, "end": 505.42, "text": "Accordingly, all of this"},
    {"i": 218, "start": 505.42, "end": 507.42, "text": "throws the standard atmosphere"},
    {"i": 219, "start": 507.42, "end": 509.42, "text": "out of equilibrium,"},
    {"i": 220, "start": 509.42, "end": 511.42, "text": "and there are fluctuations,"},
    {"i": 221, "start": 511.42, "end": 512.42, "text": "in air pressure,"},
    {"i": 222, "start": 512.42, "end": 514.42, "text": "and that gives us our whole weather system."},
    {"i": 223, "start": 514.42, "end": 516.42, "text": "And it's a really important motor"},
    {"i": 224, "start": 516.42, "end": 517.42, "text": "that"},
    {"i": 225, "start": 517.42, "end": 518.42, "text": "throws things out of balance,"},
    {"i": 226, "start": 518.42, "end": 520.42, "text": "and influences"},
    {"i": 227, "start": 520.42, "end": 521.42, "text": "different weather."},
    {"i": 228, "start": 521.42, "end": 523.42, "text": "And we'll look at this together,"},
    {"i": 229, "start": 523.42, "end": 526.61, "text": "what kind of influence that has."},
    {"i": 230, "start": 526.61, "end": 528.5, "text": "The sun,"},
    {"i": 231, "start": 528.5, "end": 530.73, "text": "that shines on the Earth,"},
    {"i": 232, "start": 530.73, "end": 532.82, "text": "warms"},
    {"i": 233, "start": 532.82, "end": 533.82, "text": "the ground,"},
    {"i": 234, "start": 533.82, "end": 534.82, "text": "that's important."},
    {"i": 235, "start": 534.82, "end": 535.82, "text": "So the sun"},
    {"i": 236, "start": 535.82, "end": 536.82, "text": "doesn't actually warm air masses"},
    {"i": 237, "start": 536.82, "end": 538.82, "text": "as it shines through them,"},
    {"i": 238, "start": 538.82, "end": 540.82, "text": "it might warm them slightly,"},
    {"i": 239, "start": 540.82, "end": 542.82, "text": "or it can't really warm them,"},
    {"i": 240, "start": 542.82, "end": 544.82, "text": "it actually only warms"},
    {"i": 241, "start": 544.82, "end": 546.82, "text": "the ground-level air layers."},
    {"i": 242, "start": 546.82, "end": 547.82, "text": "That's the air layer"},
    {"i": 243, "start": 547.82, "end": 549.82, "text": "that's really sitting on the ground,"},
    {"i": 244, "start": 549.82, "end": 551.82, "text": "with the radiation heat"},
    {"i": 245, "start": 551.82, "end": 552.82, "text": "that arises there,"},
    {"i": 246, "start": 552.82, "end": 555.82, "text": "and the ground-level air layer warms up."},
    {"i": 247, "start": 555.82, "end": 557.82, "text": "And the heating"},
    {"i": 248, "start": 557.82, "end": 559.82, "text": "of these ground-level air layers"},
    {"i": 249, "start": 559.82, "end": 561.82, "text": "varies by region around the world,"},
    {"i": 250, "start": 561.82, "end": 563.82, "text": "distributed across the globe,"},
    {"i": 251, "start": 563.82, "end": 565.82, "text": "where things warm differently."},
    {"i": 252, "start": 565.82, "end": 567.82, "text": "Regions at the equator"},
    {"i": 253, "start": 567.82, "end": 569.82, "text": "warm up more, of course,"},
    {"i": 254, "start": 569.82, "end": 570.82, "text": "than a region"},
    {"i": 255, "start": 570.82, "end": 571.82, "text": "in the polar areas."},
    {"i": 256, "start": 602.3, "end": 604.3, "text": "An air mass"},
    {"i": 257, "start": 604.3, "end": 606.3, "text": "is actually a volume of air"},
    {"i": 258, "start": 606.3, "end": 608.3, "text": "that has the same properties."},
    {"i": 259, "start": 608.3, "end": 610.3, "text": "For example warmer air masses,"},
    {"i": 260, "start": 610.3, "end": 612.3, "text": "and colder ones."},
    {"i": 261, "start": 612.3, "end": 613.3, "text": "And these are always regions"},
    {"i": 262, "start": 613.3, "end": 615.3, "text": "that, over several hundred kilometres,"},
    {"i": 263, "start": 615.3, "end": 617.3, "text": "have the same properties,"},
    {"i": 264, "start": 617.3, "end": 619.3, "text": "so the same air pressure,"},
    {"i": 265, "start": 619.3, "end": 620.3, "text": "or the same temperature,"},
    {"i": 266, "start": 620.3, "end": 621.3, "text": "or similar temperatures,"},
    {"i": 267, "start": 621.3, "end": 622.3, "text": "warmer temperatures"},
    {"i": 268, "start": 622.3, "end": 624.3, "text": "or colder temperatures."},
    {"i": 269, "start": 627.58, "end": 629.58, "text": "Basically, it works like this:"},
    {"i": 270, "start": 629.58, "end": 630.58, "text": "over regions"},
    {"i": 271, "start": 630.58, "end": 632.58, "text": "that are colder for longer"},
    {"i": 272, "start": 632.58, "end": 634.58, "text": "than the surroundings,"},
    {"i": 273, "start": 634.58, "end": 637.58, "text": "higher air pressure forms."},
    {"i": 274, "start": 637.58, "end": 638.58, "text": "And over regions"},
    {"i": 275, "start": 638.58, "end": 639.58, "text": "that are warm for longer,"},
    {"i": 276, "start": 639.58, "end": 641.58, "text": "you get"},
    {"i": 277, "start": 641.58, "end": 642.58, "text": "the formation of"},
    {"i": 278, "start": 642.58, "end": 643.58, "text": "lower pressure."},
    {"i": 279, "start": 643.58, "end": 645.58, "text": "And accordingly,"},
    {"i": 280, "start": 645.58, "end": 647.58, "text": "in the tropical regions,"},
    {"i": 281, "start": 647.58, "end": 649.58, "text": "for example, we get tropical low-pressure areas,"},
    {"i": 282, "start": 649.58, "end": 651.58, "text": "and in the polar regions"},
    {"i": 283, "start": 651.58, "end": 653.58, "text": "we get the polar high-pressure areas."},
    {"i": 284, "start": 653.58, "end": 656.58, "text": "That's how different air pressures form."},
    {"i": 285, "start": 656.58, "end": 659.58, "text": "And then the pressure areas develop"},
    {"i": 286, "start": 659.58, "end": 662.58, "text": "that we'll dive into in the next few slides."},
    {"i": 287, "start": 662.58, "end": 663.58, "text": "So,"},
    {"i": 288, "start": 663.58, "end": 664.58, "text": "that was about"},
    {"i": 289, "start": 664.58, "end": 666.58, "text": "what kind of influence"},
    {"i": 290, "start": 666.58, "end": 668.58, "text": "this has on our weather."},
    {"i": 291, "start": 668.58, "end": 669.9, "text": "You can picture it"},
    {"i": 292, "start": 669.9, "end": 671.9, "text": "as belts"},
    {"i": 293, "start": 671.9, "end": 672.9, "text": "around the world."},
    {"i": 294, "start": 672.9, "end": 673.9, "text": "Around the globe,"},
    {"i": 295, "start": 673.9, "end": 675.9, "text": "there are the so-called Hadley cells,"},
    {"i": 296, "start": 675.9, "end": 677.9, "text": "they are the low-pressure"},
    {"i": 297, "start": 677.9, "end": 678.9, "text": "and high-pressure rings."},
    {"i": 298, "start": 678.9, "end": 679.9, "text": "There are more of them"},
    {"i": 299, "start": 679.9, "end": 680.9, "text": "than what's on this graphic."},
    {"i": 300, "start": 680.9, "end": 683.0, "text": "Basically though,"},
    {"i": 301, "start": 683.0, "end": 685.0, "text": "in the tropical regions"},
    {"i": 302, "start": 685.0, "end": 686.0, "text": "you get a low-pressure belt"},
    {"i": 303, "start": 686.0, "end": 687.0, "text": "and in the polar regions"},
    {"i": 304, "start": 687.0, "end": 689.0, "text": "a high-pressure belt."},
    {"i": 305, "start": 690.0, "end": 693.03, "text": "And so we also have tropical air masses"},
    {"i": 306, "start": 693.03, "end": 695.03, "text": "and polar air masses."},
    {"i": 307, "start": 695.03, "end": 697.03, "text": "And here too we'll now"},
    {"i": 308, "start": 697.03, "end": 699.03, "text": "in the next few minutes learn"},
    {"i": 309, "start": 699.03, "end": 703.03, "text": "what kind of influence that has on our weather."},
    {"i": 310, "start": 703.03, "end": 705.77, "text": "So look here,"},
    {"i": 311, "start": 705.77, "end": 707.77, "text": "there's different heating"},
    {"i": 312, "start": 707.77, "end": 709.77, "text": "of different regions."},
    {"i": 313, "start": 709.77, "end": 711.77, "text": "Accordingly we have high-pressure areas"},
    {"i": 314, "start": 711.77, "end": 713.77, "text": "and low-pressure areas."},
    {"i": 315, "start": 713.77, "end": 715.77, "text": "And we can see here in the middle, for example,"},
    {"i": 316, "start": 715.77, "end": 716.77, "text": "the number,"},
    {"i": 317, "start": 716.77, "end": 717.77, "text": "that we can recognise,"},
    {"i": 318, "start": 717.77, "end": 719.77, "text": "from the standard atmosphere."},
    {"i": 319, "start": 719.77, "end": 722.77, "text": "The 1013.25, and as soon as"},
    {"i": 320, "start": 722.77, "end": 724.96, "text": "the air pressure drops below this."},
    {"i": 321, "start": 724.96, "end": 725.96, "text": "Below that,"},
    {"i": 322, "start": 725.96, "end": 727.96, "text": "we talk about a low-pressure area."},
    {"i": 323, "start": 727.96, "end": 729.96, "text": "Here in Europe,"},
    {"i": 324, "start": 729.96, "end": 731.96, "text": "very pronounced examples"},
    {"i": 325, "start": 731.96, "end": 732.96, "text": "of low-pressure areas,"},
    {"i": 326, "start": 732.96, "end": 735.96, "text": "we talk about 955 hectopascals,"},
    {"i": 327, "start": 735.96, "end": 737.96, "text": "and very pronounced"},
    {"i": 328, "start": 737.96, "end": 738.96, "text": "high-pressure areas,"},
    {"i": 329, "start": 738.96, "end": 741.96, "text": "we talk about 1035 hectopascals."},
    {"i": 330, "start": 741.96, "end": 742.96, "text": "Right now it's the time"},
    {"i": 331, "start": 742.96, "end": 743.96, "text": "of global warming."},
    {"i": 332, "start": 743.96, "end": 745.96, "text": "Unfortunately, the values"},
    {"i": 333, "start": 745.96, "end": 746.96, "text": "are getting more extreme."},
    {"i": 334, "start": 746.96, "end": 748.96, "text": "There are even high-pressure areas"},
    {"i": 335, "start": 748.96, "end": 752.96, "text": "that reach up to 1048 hectopascals."},
    {"i": 336, "start": 752.96, "end": 754.96, "text": "So those are very strong"},
    {"i": 337, "start": 754.96, "end": 756.96, "text": "pressure differences."},
    {"i": 338, "start": 756.96, "end": 758.96, "text": "Accordingly,"},
    {"i": 339, "start": 758.96, "end": 763.96, "text": "the"},
    {"i": 340, "start": 763.96, "end": 766.96, "text": "meteorological phenomena get stronger."},
    {"i": 341, "start": 766.96, "end": 768.96, "text": "And the stronger weather,"},
    {"i": 342, "start": 768.96, "end": 770.96, "text": "that we unfortunately keep experiencing,"},
    {"i": 343, "start": 770.96, "end": 774.4, "text": "with the storms, for example,"},
    {"i": 344, "start": 774.4, "end": 776.62, "text": "has exactly to do with these pressure fluctuations,"},
    {"i": 345, "start": 776.62, "end": 778.62, "text": "and we'll get to it later too,"},
    {"i": 346, "start": 778.62, "end": 782.62, "text": "in a high-pressure area"},
    {"i": 347, "start": 782.62, "end": 784.62, "text": "air masses sink,"},
    {"i": 348, "start": 784.62, "end": 785.62, "text": "and in a low-pressure area"},
    {"i": 349, "start": 785.62, "end": 786.62, "text": "air masses rise."},
    {"i": 350, "start": 786.62, "end": 788.62, "text": "That's very important later"},
    {"i": 351, "start": 788.62, "end": 790.62, "text": "for flying weather,"},
    {"i": 352, "start": 790.62, "end": 792.62, "text": "which we'll get to."},
    {"i": 353, "start": 792.62, "end": 793.62, "text": "And basically,"},
    {"i": 354, "start": 793.62, "end": 795.62, "text": "like every gas"},
    {"i": 355, "start": 795.62, "end": 797.62, "text": "or every liquid,"},
    {"i": 356, "start": 797.62, "end": 799.62, "text": "air masses have"},
    {"i": 357, "start": 799.62, "end": 802.62, "text": "the need to equalise pressure."},
    {"i": 358, "start": 802.62, "end": 803.62, "text": "That means"},
    {"i": 359, "start": 803.62, "end": 805.62, "text": "air masses will always"},
    {"i": 360, "start": 805.62, "end": 807.62, "text": "flow from high pressure to low pressure,"},
    {"i": 361, "start": 807.62, "end": 809.62, "text": "because pressure wants to equalise."},
    {"i": 362, "start": 809.62, "end": 811.82, "text": "And accordingly,"},
    {"i": 363, "start": 811.82, "end": 813.82, "text": "especially for us when waiting,"},
    {"i": 364, "start": 813.82, "end": 815.82, "text": "or in the lower air layers,"},
    {"i": 365, "start": 815.82, "end": 817.82, "text": "the air flow is important,"},
    {"i": 366, "start": 817.82, "end": 819.82, "text": "that air flows from high"},
    {"i": 367, "start": 819.82, "end": 822.82, "text": "to low, and accordingly"},
    {"i": 368, "start": 822.82, "end": 824.82, "text": "wind develops,"},
    {"i": 369, "start": 824.82, "end": 825.82, "text": "the wind systems"},
    {"i": 370, "start": 825.82, "end": 827.82, "text": "that you can feel,"},
    {"i": 371, "start": 827.82, "end": 829.82, "text": "when the wind blows."},
    {"i": 372, "start": 829.82, "end": 831.82, "text": "And so we get"},
    {"i": 373, "start": 831.82, "end": 833.82, "text": "the high-altitude flow,"},
    {"i": 374, "start": 833.82, "end": 835.82, "text": "which is important for us"},
    {"i": 375, "start": 835.82, "end": 837.82, "text": "to recognise wind directions"},
    {"i": 376, "start": 837.82, "end": 841.0, "text": "and read them from the charts."},
    {"i": 377, "start": 841.0, "end": 844.03, "text": "Then we come to isobar charts"},
    {"i": 378, "start": 844.03, "end": 845.03, "text": "wait,"},
    {"i": 379, "start": 845.03, "end": 846.03, "text": "you might have heard of those"},
    {"i": 380, "start": 846.03, "end": 848.03, "text": "or read about them in the theory book."},
    {"i": 381, "start": 848.03, "end": 850.03, "text": "There are weather charts"},
    {"i": 382, "start": 850.03, "end": 852.03, "text": "where exactly the weather phenomena"},
    {"i": 383, "start": 852.03, "end": 853.03, "text": "that we just"},
    {"i": 384, "start": 853.03, "end": 854.03, "text": "discussed"},
    {"i": 385, "start": 854.03, "end": 855.38, "text": "are described."},
    {"i": 386, "start": 855.38, "end": 856.38, "text": "Weather charts,"},
    {"i": 387, "start": 856.38, "end": 857.38, "text": "they're created"},
    {"i": 388, "start": 857.38, "end": 859.38, "text": "partly from current measurements,"},
    {"i": 389, "start": 859.38, "end": 860.38, "text": "where you measure with barometers"},
    {"i": 390, "start": 860.38, "end": 862.38, "text": "or air pressure."},
    {"i": 391, "start": 862.38, "end": 865.38, "text": "And of course the computer models,"},
    {"i": 392, "start": 865.38, "end": 867.38, "text": "that based on the measurements"},
    {"i": 393, "start": 867.38, "end": 868.38, "text": "try to predict"},
    {"i": 394, "start": 868.38, "end": 870.38, "text": "the weather,"},
    {"i": 395, "start": 870.38, "end": 871.18, "text": "and"},
    {"i": 396, "start": 871.18, "end": 872.38, "text": "compute it in advance."},
    {"i": 397, "start": 872.38, "end": 874.38, "text": "And then come"},
    {"i": 398, "start": 874.38, "end": 875.38, "text": "the funny-looking weather charts,"},
    {"i": 399, "start": 875.38, "end": 877.38, "text": "which we'll now look at more closely,"},
    {"i": 400, "start": 877.38, "end": 880.38, "text": "how to read them."},
    {"i": 401, "start": 880.38, "end": 882.38, "text": "Isobar charts,"},
    {"i": 402, "start": 882.38, "end": 884.38, "text": "isobars,"},
    {"i": 403, "start": 884.38, "end": 885.38, "text": "those are the lines"},
    {"i": 404, "start": 885.38, "end": 887.74, "text": "you see there,"},
    {"i": 405, "start": 887.74, "end": 889.74, "text": "isobars,"},
    {"i": 406, "start": 889.74, "end": 890.74, "text": "described,"},
    {"i": 407, "start": 890.74, "end": 891.74, "text": "are the regions"},
    {"i": 408, "start": 891.74, "end": 892.74, "text": "that have the same air pressure,"},
    {"i": 409, "start": 892.74, "end": 893.74, "text": "or the same air pressure,"},
    {"i": 410, "start": 893.74, "end": 895.74, "text": "simply put,"},
    {"i": 411, "start": 895.74, "end": 896.8, "text": "where it prevails."},
    {"i": 412, "start": 896.8, "end": 898.8, "text": "So for example,"},
    {"i": 413, "start": 898.8, "end": 899.8, "text": "1025 hectopascals,"},
    {"i": 414, "start": 899.8, "end": 901.8, "text": "you can't see it well here,"},
    {"i": 415, "start": 901.8, "end": 902.8, "text": "in the next chart"},
    {"i": 416, "start": 902.8, "end": 903.8, "text": "you can see it better."},
    {"i": 417, "start": 903.8, "end": 904.8, "text": "And everywhere"},
    {"i": 418, "start": 904.8, "end": 905.8, "text": "the lines run,"},
    {"i": 419, "start": 905.8, "end": 907.8, "text": "calculated at sea level,"},
    {"i": 420, "start": 907.8, "end": 908.8, "text": "that's very important,"},
    {"i": 421, "start": 908.8, "end": 910.8, "text": "the pressure is calculated"},
    {"i": 422, "start": 910.8, "end": 911.8, "text": "at sea level,"},
    {"i": 423, "start": 911.8, "end": 913.8, "text": "where the same air pressure prevails."},
    {"i": 424, "start": 913.8, "end": 916.8, "text": "That's where the name isobar chart comes from."},
    {"i": 425, "start": 916.8, "end": 917.8, "text": "Iso means the same,"},
    {"i": 426, "start": 917.8, "end": 918.8, "text": "bar"},
    {"i": 427, "start": 918.8, "end": 919.8, "text": "is pressure,"},
    {"i": 428, "start": 919.8, "end": 920.8, "text": "everywhere"},
    {"i": 429, "start": 920.8, "end": 921.8, "text": "where the same air pressure prevails,"},
    {"i": 430, "start": 921.8, "end": 923.8, "text": "such a line gets drawn."},
    {"i": 431, "start": 923.8, "end": 926.41, "text": "And on such an isobar chart"},
    {"i": 432, "start": 926.41, "end": 928.41, "text": "fronts are often drawn in,"},
    {"i": 433, "start": 928.41, "end": 929.41, "text": "naturally,"},
    {"i": 434, "start": 929.41, "end": 930.41, "text": "we'll come back to that later"},
    {"i": 435, "start": 930.41, "end": 932.41, "text": "in the course,"},
    {"i": 436, "start": 932.41, "end": 934.54, "text": "what these fronts"},
    {"i": 437, "start": 934.54, "end": 936.86, "text": "are about."}
  ]
}
